==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disputatious
<hw>Dis`pu*ta"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Inclined to
dispute; apt to civil or controvert; characterized by dispute; <as>as, a
<ex>disputatious</ex> person or temper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Christian doctrine of a future life was no recommendation of
the new religion to the wits and philosophers of that
<qex>disputations</qex> period.</q> <rj><qau>Buckminster.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Dis`pu*ta"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Dis`pu*ta"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disputative</ent>⟦br⟧
